---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Layout title="Privacy Policy — Dromos" description="Dromos privacy policy — what data we collect, why, and how we handle it.">
  <Header />

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-10">Last updated: April 2026</p>

    <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-8">

      <p>Dromos ("we", "our", "the app") is a triathlon training planner for iOS. This policy explains what data we collect, why, and how we handle it.</p>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">1. Data We Collect</h2>
        <p class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Account information</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-gray-600 space-y-1 mb-4">
          <li>Email address and password (for authentication)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Personal information (provided during onboarding)</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-gray-600 space-y-1 mb-4">
          <li>Biological sex, date of birth, and weight</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Training preferences (provided during onboarding)</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-gray-600 space-y-1 mb-4">
          <li>Race objective and target date</li>
          <li>Target finish time</li>
          <li>Performance metrics: VMA, CSS, and FTP (optional)</li>
          <li>Years of experience and current weekly training hours</li>
          <li>Weekly sport availability (swim, bike, run days) and daily training durations</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Strava activity data (optional, if you connect Strava)</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-gray-600 space-y-1 mb-4">
          <li>Activity type, duration, distance, GPS route, heart rate, and power data from your Strava account</li>
          <li>Only synced with your explicit authorization via Strava OAuth</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Generated data</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-gray-600 space-y-1 mb-4">
          <li>Your personalized training plan, including weekly phases and individual sessions, generated by our system based on the information above</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Technical data</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-gray-600 space-y-1">
          <li>IP address and standard server logs, collected automatically when you use the app</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-gray-600 space-y-1">
          <li>To create and manage your account</li>
          <li>To generate a personalized triathlon training plan using AI</li>
          <li>To display your plan and profile within the app</li>
          <li>To match Strava activities to your planned sessions (if Strava is connected)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mt-3">We do not use your data for advertising, profiling, or any purpose unrelated to providing the Dromos service.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">3. AI-Generated Plans</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600">Your onboarding data (goals, metrics, availability) is sent to an AI model on our server to generate your training plan. This processing happens server-side. The AI does not retain your data after generating the plan.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">4. Data Sharing</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">We do not sell or rent your personal data. We share data only with the following processors required to operate the service:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Supabase</strong> — Data storage and authentication infrastructure. Your profile, training plan, and activity data are stored on Supabase servers.</li>
          <li><strong>OpenAI</strong> — AI model used server-side to generate your personalized training plan. Only your onboarding data (goals, metrics, availability) is sent. OpenAI does not retain your data after processing.</li>
          <li><strong>Strava</strong> — If you choose to connect Strava, your activity data is fetched from Strava's API via OAuth with your explicit consent. You can disconnect Strava at any time from the Profile screen.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mt-3">No other third-party services receive your data.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">5. Data Security</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-gray-600 space-y-1">
          <li>Passwords are hashed and never stored in plain text</li>
          <li>All data is protected by row-level security policies, ensuring you can only access your own data</li>
          <li>All communication between the app and our servers is encrypted via HTTPS</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">6. Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600">We retain your data for as long as your account is active. When you delete your account, all associated data — your profile, training plans, and sessions — is permanently and automatically deleted. There is no recovery after deletion.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">7. Your Rights</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600">You can:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-gray-600 space-y-1">
          <li>Access and update your personal data via the Profile screen in the app</li>
          <li>Disconnect Strava at any time from the Profile screen</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your account and all associated data</li>
          <li>Contact us with any questions about your data</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">8. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600">Dromos is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect data from children under 13.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">9. Analytics and Tracking</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600">Dromos does not use analytics services, crash reporting tools, advertising SDKs, or any form of user tracking.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600">If we make material changes to this policy, we will update the "Last updated" date above. Continued use of the app after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">11. Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600">For privacy questions or data requests, contact us at:<br/>
        <a href="mailto:support@getdromos.com" class="text-brand hover:underline">support@getdromos.com</a></p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
